report.measDesc: The dataset is converted to file geodatabase (FGDB) format using tools in ArcGIS. The geometry is checked, and if needed repaired.
After processing, the dataset is checked for drawing display and number of records and file sizes compared with source materials.

The geospatial part of this data set was mathematically generated using the ARC/INFO® GRID™ extension. In this manner, the locations were computed. The positional accuracy is limited only by the resolution of the data set, which is less than a meter.

prcStep.stepDesc: The following steps were performed by Esri: Generated the geospatial part of this data set mathematically using the ARC/INFO® GRID extension. Added unique values attribute.

The following steps were performed by Esri: Extracted data set from Esri Data & Maps Volume 1. Created ArcGIS® layer file (.lyr). Created projection file (.prj). Created spatial indices. Converted the data set to SDC.

The following steps were performed by Esri: Corrected the north and east geographic extents. Renamed WRLD30_ID to WRLD_ID and reduced its width. Converted the data set to SDC. Created ArcGIS® layer file (.lyr), projection file (.prj), and spatial indices.
Converted the dataset into a file geodatabase.
